<title type="html"><![CDATA[11/24(Thu)How to Improve Muscular Strength and Definition/South Korea Halloween crush kills 120, injures 100 (Host: May)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=674&amp;p=702#p702"><![CDATA[
11/24(Thu)How to Improve Muscular Strength and Definition/South Korea Halloween crush kills 120, injures 100 (Host: May)<br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:05-7:40 pm Session 1: Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Individual Presentation<br />8:00-8:05 pm Break<br />8:05-8:40 pm Session 2: Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Individual Presentation<br /><br />We will hold a zoom meeting only.<br /><br />Zoom meeting: Please click the link below<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ...<br />Meeting ID:929 8726 6213<br />Password:112233<br /><br />-------------------------------------------- <br /><br />Session 1: How to Improve Muscular Strength and Definition<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.verywellfit.com/how-to-increase-muscular-strength-3496121#toc-exercise-to-improve-strength-and-definition">https://www.verywellfit.com/how-to-incr ... definition</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions<br />1.Do you do strength training or weightlifting to improve strength? Share your experience with us. What are the reasons If you do not? <br />2.How often do you go to gymnasium? What was it like going to the gym for the first time? Do you have anything about gyms to share?<br />3. What do you think of muscular boys/girls?It is said that most muscular men are very strong, but not very smart,do you agree? If possible, how would you shape your body? sturdy /Plump/slim?<br />4.People over the age of 50 are more likely to develop sarcopenia(肌少症). Do you have any prevention plans?<br /><br /><br />Session 2: Korea Halloween crush kills 120, injures 100 – officials<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-63440849">https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-63440849</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1. What could have caused this disaster? Was it possible to avoid it?<br />2. The Taipei City Government has held many New Year's Eve activities; the number of people were no less than that of Seoul. In your opinion, are the routes in and out properly managed/arranged? Or were they lucky not to go wrong?<br />3. After this disaster would you restrict you/ your child from participating in such activities? Tell you opinions.<br />4. What do you know best about CPR? Are you able to perform CPR if needed urgently? Do you have any stories about CPR?<br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次(含實體及線上會議)後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放的心與熱情來參加全英文會話聚會!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38674">Louie Wang</a> — Sun Nov 20, 2022 12:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
